[ctns_make id='gen_linear_func_slope_formula_linear_function']

  [ctns_front style='']
Slope Formula<br/>Linear Function
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>slope</strong> of a linear function is the ratio $|\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}=\frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x}|$ for two points $$(x_2,y_2)$$ and $$(x_1,y_1)$$ on the graph of the linear function.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
Slope formula -- linear function
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
The slope of a linear function is the ratio of the quantity why sub two minus why sub one -- divided by -- the quantity exx sub two minus exx sub one -- for two points on the line -- exx sub two why sub two -- and -- exx sub one why sub one 
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
